title.narrative: CHILDREN, ADOLESCENTS, FAMILIES AND COMMUNITIES

description.narrative: Children, adolescents, their families and communities, especially the most vulnerable, develop life and self-care skills in harmonious and protective family and community environments that foster positive behavior to prevent violence, abuse and exploitation., which contributes to Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, children and adolescents, especially the most vulnerable, will grow up in a protective environment that fosters the restitution of rights against all types of violence, abuse and exploitation

title.narrative: Children, adolescents, their families and communities, especially the most vulnerable, develop life and self-care skills inharmonious and protective family and community environments that foster positive behavior to prevent violence, abuse andexploitation.

description.narrative: UNICEF implemented programmes to develop self-care skills, positive behavior to prevent violence, abuse and exploitation, and a harmonious and protective family and community environment. As a result, 9,916 mothers, fathers and caregivers participated in the "Values Schools" and 29,366 children, fathers and mothers from the communities affected by hurricanes Eta/Iota on the North Caribbean Coast received psycho-social support, and support for the prevention and detection of violence against children, including gender violence. Nineteen networks of fathers, mothers and caregivers were created for the protection of children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:23/01/2022
